# Styling Conventions

Consistent styling through design system hierarchy and scoped CSS patterns.

## Default Behavior

### Design System Hierarchy

Use this order when selecting UI components:

```
1. NgZorro (primary)     → Use for ALL standard UI components
2. Angular Material      → ONLY when NgZorro lacks the component
3. Bootstrap utilities   → ONLY for layout/spacing (not components)
4. Custom CSS           → Last resort, scoped to component
```

### NgZorro First

NgZorro is the default for all UI components.

> **Locale requirement:** NgZorro defaults to `zh_CN`. Always register `provideNzI18n(en_US)` in `app.config.ts` or every popconfirm, modal, date picker, and pagination component will render labels in Chinese. See `angular-patterns.mdc` for the full setup snippet.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: NgZorro components -->
<button nz-button nzType="primary">Save</button>
<nz-input-group>
  <input nz-input placeholder="Search..." />
</nz-input-group>
<nz-table [nzData]="items()">...</nz-table>
<nz-modal [(nzVisible)]="isOpen">...</nz-modal>
<nz-select [(ngModel)]="selected">...</nz-select>
<nz-date-picker [(ngModel)]="date"></nz-date-picker>

<!-- ❌ Avoid: Material when NgZorro has equivalent -->
<button mat-raised-button>Save</button>
<mat-form-field><input matInput /></mat-form-field>
```

### Bootstrap for Layout Only

Use Bootstrap utilities for spacing and layout, not components.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Bootstrap utilities for layout -->
<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center gap-3">
  <h2 class="mb-0">Title</h2>
  <button nz-button>Action</button>  <!-- NgZorro component -->
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">...</div>
  <div class="col-md-6">...</div>
</div>

<!-- ❌ Avoid: Bootstrap components -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
<div class="card">...</div>
```

### Component-Scoped Styles

Keep styles scoped to components using Angular's default encapsulation.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Scoped styles (ViewEncapsulation.Emulated is default)
@Component({
  selector: 'app-user-card',
  styleUrl: './user-card.component.scss'
  // No need to specify ViewEncapsulation - Emulated is default
})
```

```scss
// user-card.component.scss
// ✅ Default: Component-specific styles
.user-card {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
}

.user-card__avatar {
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
}
```

### CSS Custom Properties for Theming

Use CSS custom properties (design tokens) instead of hardcoded values.

```scss
// ✅ Default: Design tokens
.card {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  background: var(--bg-surface);
  color: var(--text-primary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

// ❌ Avoid: Hardcoded values
.card {
  padding: 16px;
  background: #ffffff;
  color: #333333;
  border-radius: 8px;
}
```

## Rationale

1. **Visual consistency** - One design language throughout the app
2. **Smaller bundle** - Don't ship multiple component libraries
3. **Maintainability** - Change theme in one place, applies everywhere
4. **Accessibility** - NgZorro handles a11y consistently across components
5. **Developer experience** - Learn one API, use everywhere

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. Material When NgZorro Lacks Component

Use Material only when NgZorro doesn't have an equivalent component.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Material Stepper (NgZorro's nz-steps has different UX)
import { MatStepperModule } from '@angular/material/stepper';

@Component({
  imports: [MatStepperModule],
  template: `
    <!-- Document why Material is used -->
    <!-- Using Material Stepper: NgZorro nz-steps doesn't support linear validation -->
    <mat-stepper linear>
      <mat-step [stepControl]="firstFormGroup">...</mat-step>
    </mat-stepper>
  `
})
```

**Always document why** in a comment above the component.

### 2. Global Styles for Design Tokens

Define design tokens and resets in global stylesheets.

```scss
// styles/tokens.scss - ✅ Exception: Global design tokens
:root {
  // Spacing
  --spacing-xs: 4px;
  --spacing-sm: 8px;
  --spacing-md: 16px;
  --spacing-lg: 24px;
  --spacing-xl: 32px;

  // Colors (align with NgZorro theme)
  --primary: #1890ff;
  --success: #52c41a;
  --warning: #faad14;
  --error: #ff4d4f;
  
  // Surfaces
  --bg-surface: #ffffff;
  --bg-elevated: #fafafa;
  --text-primary: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
  --text-secondary: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
  
  // Effects
  --border-radius: 6px;
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

// Dark theme
[data-theme='dark'] {
  --bg-surface: #141414;
  --bg-elevated: #1f1f1f;
  --text-primary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  --text-secondary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
}
```

### 3. NgZorro Theme Overrides

Override NgZorro's Less variables or use CSS custom properties.

```scss
// styles/ng-zorro-overrides.scss - ✅ Exception: DS customization
// Override NgZorro CSS custom properties
:root {
  --ant-primary-color: #your-brand-color;
  --ant-border-radius-base: 6px;
}

// Or target specific components
.ant-btn-primary {
  // Only override when brand requirements differ from defaults
}
```

### 4. ::ng-deep for Third-Party Styling

Use `::ng-deep` sparingly for third-party component overrides.

```scss
// ✅ Exception: Third-party component that can't be styled otherwise
:host ::ng-deep {
  .third-party-component {
    // Document why ::ng-deep is necessary
    // NgZorro modal content needs custom scrollbar
    &::-webkit-scrollbar {
      width: 8px;
    }
  }
}
```

**Rules for ::ng-deep:**
- Isolate in dedicated `_overrides.scss` files
- Always scope with `:host`
- Document why it's necessary
- Prefer CSS custom properties or component APIs first

### 5. ViewEncapsulation.None for Theme Files

Only for global theme overrides that must pierce encapsulation.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Theme override component
@Component({
  selector: 'app-theme-overrides',
  template: '',
  styleUrl: './theme-overrides.scss',
  encapsulation: ViewEncapsulation.None  // Document why
})
export class ThemeOverridesComponent {}
```

## Anti-Patterns

```html
<!-- ❌ Mixing design systems for same component type -->
<button nz-button>NgZorro Button</button>
<button mat-button>Material Button</button>  <!-- Same page! -->

<!-- ❌ Bootstrap components (use NgZorro instead) -->
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">...</div>
</div>

<!-- ❌ Inline styles -->
<div style="padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 20px;">

<!-- ❌ Hardcoded colors -->
<div class="header" style="background: #1890ff;">
```

```scss
// ❌ !important to fight the design system
.ant-btn {
  background: red !important;
  border-radius: 0 !important;
}

// ❌ Hardcoded values instead of tokens
.container {
  padding: 16px;
  color: #333;
}

// ❌ Deeply nested selectors
.page .content .card .header .title span {
  font-size: 14px;
}

// ❌ Global styles in component files
// (put in styles/ folder instead)
body {
  font-family: sans-serif;
}
```

## File Organization

```
src/
├── styles/
│   ├── _tokens.scss         # Design tokens (CSS custom properties)
│   ├── _reset.scss          # CSS reset/normalize
│   ├── _typography.scss     # Global typography
│   ├── _utilities.scss      # Custom utility classes (if needed)
│   ├── _ng-zorro.scss       # NgZorro theme overrides
│   └── styles.scss          # Main entry (imports all above)
│
├── app/
│   └── features/
│       └── users/
│           └── components/
│               └── user-card/
│                   ├── user-card.component.ts
│                   └── user-card.component.scss  # Scoped styles only
```

## NgZorro Component Quick Reference

| Need | NgZorro Component |
|------|-------------------|
| Buttons | `nz-button` |
| Forms | `nz-form`, `nz-input`, `nz-select`, `nz-checkbox`, `nz-radio` |
| Data Display | `nz-table`, `nz-list`, `nz-card`, `nz-descriptions` |
| Feedback | `nz-alert`, `nz-message`, `nz-notification`, `nz-modal` |
| Navigation | `nz-menu`, `nz-tabs`, `nz-breadcrumb`, `nz-pagination` |
| Data Entry | `nz-date-picker`, `nz-time-picker`, `nz-upload`, `nz-rate` |
| Layout | `nz-layout`, `nz-grid` (or Bootstrap grid) |
| Loading | `nz-spin`, `nz-skeleton` |

## Responsive Patterns

```scss
// ✅ Use NgZorro's breakpoints (align with Bootstrap)
// xs: <576px, sm: ≥576px, md: ≥768px, lg: ≥992px, xl: ≥1200px, xxl: ≥1600px

// Mobile-first approach
.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 1200px) {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }
}
```

```html
<!-- ✅ NgZorro responsive grid -->
<div nz-row [nzGutter]="16">
  <div nz-col [nzXs]="24" [nzSm]="12" [nzMd]="8">
    <app-card />
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ✅ Bootstrap responsive utilities -->
<div class="d-none d-md-block">Desktop only</div>
<div class="d-md-none">Mobile only</div>
```
